      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "If we are in the context of the asker&#39;s question, then we are talking about instance methods.  Using static means that if thread 1 calls instance1.DoSomething() and thread 2 calls instance2.DoSomething, the second call will block even though it is a completely different object.  thread2&#39;s call shouldn&#39;t block unless someone is calling DoSomething on <b>the same object</b>.  Not saying you are wrong, but saying it is important to understand the effect of using static here, because it may cause poor performance by blocking globally instead of on a per instance basis."
