      "body" : "@earcam and your question is? That statement is true. The vast majority of classes have no requirement to be thread-safe, will not be tested for thread-safety, and <i>having</i> thread-safety will impact performance. The number of types that genuinely need to worry about threads is very small - intentionally synchronized collections, multiplexers, etc."
